sentences: Edicson Ruiz (born 11 May 1985 in Caracas, Venezuela) is a Venezuelan double-bass player.
In 2001, he was awarded the first prize in the youth solo competition at the International Society of Bassists convention, held in Indianapolis.

At age 17, Ruiz became the youngest member of the Berlin Philharmonic Orchestra, the second in the Philharmonic history after a harp player in the 19th century; he is also the first Hispanic-American musician to join the Berlin Philharmonic Orchestra.
After his first concert in Germany, he was offered a place in the Berlin Philharmonic, becoming a full member after one year of training.
